data.text:
This painting is one of three Steve Cox air racer works featured in the January 2021, issue of Air Classics magazine accompanying Tim Weinschenker's story: Cleveland’s Forgotten1947 Air Racers.

At the 1947, Cleveland Air races one of the most eye catching racers was the Lockheed P-38J lightning owned by J. D. Reed and flown by Charles Walling Jr. Reed put a boatload of cash into the modifications to Race #14, and Walling was able to take an early lead from Tony Levier in his P-38L Race #3 during the Lightning only "Sohio" trophy race. Levier went on to win the Race at an average speed of 360.866 mph, while Walling took second at 351.785 mph.

*This original work is available for purchase. Painting size in inches: 18 x 24. Contact Steve Cox by the phone number listed on this website for more information. Please reference "Sky Ranger."

Signed prints may be ordered through this website by clicking on the "add to cart" button. Print size in inches: image 16 x 20 on 18 x 22 paper.
